**1. How high would you have to count before you would use the letter "A" in the English language spelling of a whole number?**

The first number whose English spelling contains the letter "A" is **one thousand** (1,000).  
- "One" has no A.  
- "Two," "three," "four," "five," "six," "seven," "eight," "nine," "ten," "eleven," "twelve," "thirteen," "fourteen," "fifteen," "sixteen," "seventeen," "eighteen," "nineteen," "twenty," "twenty-one," ... "twenty-nine," "thirty," ... "ninety-nine," "one hundred," "one hundred one," ... "nine hundred ninety-nine."  
- The first time the letter "A" appears is in **"one thousand"** (the "a" in "thousand").

